// BT-2208: Stable base fixture for SystemNavigation instVarReadersOf:in: /
// instVarWritersOf:in: E2E tests.
//
// Provides test-owned classes/slots so the assertions do not depend on live
// stdlib content (which can churn across unrelated refactors).
//
// Design choices (STABLE — do not rename slots/methods or edit bodies):
//   - `state: tally` is the instance slot under test:
//       * `readTally`  reads it (read only)
//       * `bumpTally`  reads AND writes it in one method (`self.tally := self.tally + 1`)
//       * `clearTally` writes it only (`self.tally := 0`)
//   - `state: untouched` is declared but never read or written — validates the
//     "declared-but-untouched slot returns []" contract.
//   - `classState: spawnCount` is a class-side instance variable, touched only
//     by class-side methods — validates the metaclass walk:
//       * class `bumpSpawnCount` reads AND writes it
//       * class `readSpawnCount` reads it only
// `InstVarChild` (instvar_fixture_child.bt) subclasses this and touches the
// inherited `tally` slot, validating the allSubclasses walk.

Actor subclass: InstVarFixture
  state: tally = 0
  state: untouched = 0
  classState: spawnCount = 0

  // Class-side: reads AND writes the class-side ivar `spawnCount`.
  class bumpSpawnCount =>
    self.spawnCount := self.spawnCount + 1
    self.spawnCount

  // Class-side: reads the class-side ivar `spawnCount` only.
  class readSpawnCount => self.spawnCount

  // Reads `tally` only.
  readTally => self.tally

  // Reads AND writes `tally` in one method.
  bumpTally => self.tally := self.tally + 1

  // Writes `tally` only (RHS is a literal).
  clearTally => self.tally := 0
